PSEUDOCODE – ROAD ACCIDENT DETECTION SYSTEM

Algorithm 1: Data Acquisition and Video Preparation
BEGIN
CONNECT Google Drive
SET dataset_folder_path
READ all video files from dataset folder
FOR each video file IN dataset folder DO
    RENAME video into standard format
    Example: video1.mp4, video2.mp4, ...
END FOR
SORT videos in ascending order
COUNT total number of videos
DISPLAY total videos

INSTALL required libraries
•	YOLOv8
•	OpenCV
•	Pandas
•	NumPy
•	Torch

IMPORT all required libraries
CHECK GPU availability
END

Algorithm 2: Vehicle Detection using YOLOv8
BEGIN
LOAD pretrained YOLOv8 model


FOR each input video DO
    OPEN video using OpenCV
    WHILE video frames are available DO
        READ current frame
        APPLY YOLOv8 object detection on frame

        DETECT vehicles such as:
•	Car
•	Bus
•	Truck
•	Motorcycle
        DRAW bounding boxes around detected vehicles
        STORE:
•	Vehicle ID
•	Bounding box coordinates
•	Detection confidence
•	Frame number

    END WHILE
    SAVE detection results
END FOR
END

Algorithm 3: Object Tracking and CSV Generation
BEGIN
FOR each detected vehicle DO
    ASSIGN unique tracking ID
    TRACK vehicle movement across consecutive frames
    EXTRACT:
•	X coordinate
•	Y coordinate
•	Width

•	Height
•	Frame number
    STORE tracking information into CSV file

END FOR
SAVE CSV file
END

Algorithm 4: Optical Flow Estimation
BEGIN
FOR each pair of consecutive frames DO
    CONVERT frames into grayscale
    APPLY optical flow algorithm
    CALCULATE motion vectors of moving vehicles

    ESTIMATE:
•	Direction of movement
•	Magnitude of movement
•	Motion consistency
    STORE motion information
END FOR
END

Algorithm 5: Speed Calculation
BEGIN
READ tracking CSV file

FOR each tracked vehicle DO

    CALCULATE displacement between consecutive frames
    COMPUTE vehicle speed using:

        Speed = Distance / Time
    STORE speed values

END FOR
SAVE updated CSV file
END

Algorithm 6: Speed Drop Analysis
BEGIN
FOR each vehicle DO
    CALCULATE difference between previous speed and current speed
    IF sudden speed reduction occurs THEN
        MARK speed_drop_flag = TRUE
    ELSE
        MARK speed_drop_flag = FALSE
    END IF
END FOR
END

Algorithm 7: Collision Detection using IoU
BEGIN
FOR each pair of detected vehicles DO
    CALCULATE Intersection over Union (IoU)
    IF IoU value exceeds threshold THEN
        MARK collision_detected = TRUE
    ELSE
        MARK collision_detected = FALSE
    END IF

END FOR

STORE collision results
END

Algorithm 8: Temporal Consistency Validation
BEGIN
FOR each detected collision event DO
    CHECK whether collision exists across multiple frames
    IF collision persists for required number of frames THEN
        MARK temporal_consistent = TRUE
    ELSE
        MARK temporal_consistent = FALSE
    END IF
END FOR
END

Algorithm 9: Final Accident Confirmation
BEGIN
FOR each frame DO
    CALCULATE accident score using:
•	Collision detection
•	Speed drop
•	Temporal consistency
•	Motion abnormality

    COMPUTE final score
    IF final score >= threshold THEN
        MARK accident_confirmed = TRUE
    ELSE
        MARK accident_confirmed = FALSE
    END IF


END FOR
GENERATE final accident report
END

Algorithm 10: Anomaly Detection
BEGIN
FOR each vehicle movement pattern DO
    ANALYZE abnormal behavior such as:
•	Sudden stop

•	Sudden direction change
•	Irregular movement
    COMPUTE anomaly score
    STORE anomaly results
END FOR
END

Algorithm 11: Confidence Scoring
BEGIN
FOR each detected accident DO
    COMBINE:
•	Detection confidence
•	Collision score
•	Speed variation
•	Temporal consistency
    CALCULATE confidence score
    ASSIGN confidence level

END FOR
END


Algorithm 12: Severity Assessment Module
Step 12.1 – Collision Intensity
BEGIN
FOR each confirmed accident DO
    MEASURE collision intensity using:
•	Vehicle overlap

•	Speed impact
•	Motion force
    ASSIGN collision intensity level
END FOR
END

Step 12.2 – Speed Reduction Score
BEGIN
FOR each accident event DO
    CALCULATE percentage of speed reduction
    IF reduction is high THEN
        ASSIGN higher severity score
    ELSE
        ASSIGN lower severity score
    END IF
END FOR
END

Step 12.3 – Immobility Check
BEGIN
FOR each detected vehicle DO

    CHECK vehicle speed after collision
    IF vehicle remains stationary for long duration THEN

        SET immobility_flag = TRUE
    ELSE
        SET immobility_flag = FALSE
    END IF
END FOR
END

Step 12.4 – Severity Classification
BEGIN
FOR each confirmed accident DO
    CALCULATE severity score using:
•	Collision intensity
•	Speed reduction
•	Immobility duration

•	Anomaly score

    IF score is low THEN
        LABEL accident as Minor
    ELSE IF score is medium THEN
        LABEL accident as Major
    ELSE
        LABEL accident as Critical
    END IF

END FOR
GENERATE final severity report
END

Overall System Workflow
BEGIN

COLLECT traffic videos
